x4freetext: TANGRA setup on the basis of ING-27
Deuterons of ~80 keV on tritium target.
Maximum intensity of the neutron flux in full solid
introduced into a rectangular aluminum container of
64-pixel silicon alpha detector for detection of
3.5 MeV alphas from d+t -> n+alpha reaction.
18 scintillation detectors based on BGO crystals
of 76 mm diameter, 65 mm thickness; arranged in
horizontal plane along a circle of 750 mm radius with
a  step of 14 degrees of angle. For gamma detection.
HPGe crystal of 57.5 mm diameter, 66.6 mm
thickness. Lead collimator - to suppress the background
. All detectors were calibrated by reference gamma
. ADCM-32 analog-to-digital converter based on two
.Gamma spectra were measured in coincidence by HPGe
. Energies and partial cross sections were measured
by detector system based on BGO .
